---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Licence terms"
  description="RevAudio plugin end-user licence agreement (EULA)."
>
  <section class="plugin-detail">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 760px;">
      <h1>Licence terms</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: 2026-05-04 &middot; <em>Pre-launch placeholder &mdash; replace with reviewed legal text before commerce goes live.</em></p>

      <h2>1. Grant of licence</h2>
      <p>
        When you purchase a RevAudio plugin, you (the &ldquo;Licensee&rdquo;) are granted a non-exclusive,
        non-transferable, perpetual licence to install and use the plugin on any computer you personally own.
        The licence is for a single user; you may not share it with others.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Updates</h2>
      <p>
        Free updates are included within the same major version (e.g. all v1.x updates are free for v1.0 owners).
        Major version upgrades may be offered as separate paid upgrades, typically at a discounted price.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Refunds</h2>
      <p>
        Within 14 days of purchase, you may request a full refund by emailing
        <a href="mailto:support@revaudio.net">support@revaudio.net</a>. After refund, your licence is revoked.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Restrictions</h2>
      <p>
        You may not redistribute, resell, sublicense, reverse engineer, or attempt to bypass the licence enforcement
        of any RevAudio plugin. You may not use a single licence on machines belonging to other people.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Warranty</h2>
      <p>
        RevAudio plugins are provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo; without warranty of any kind. While we measure, null-test, and
        audit every release, audio software interacts with countless hosts, drivers, and configurations &mdash; we cannot
        guarantee compatibility with every setup.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, RevAudio shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or
        consequential damages arising from the use or inability to use the plugins.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:info@revaudio.net">info@revaudio.net</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
